    "body": "So that they're based on the types of the argument rather than the slightly arbitrary order of the types within a fusd type. This should mean they keep being right if the fused type is expanded.\r\n\r\nFor an example fused function:\r\n\r\n```\r\n# pxd file\r\ncdef fused IntOrFloat:\r\n    int\r\n    float\r\n\r\ncdef fused FloatOrObject:\r\n    float\r\n    object\r\n\r\ncdef IntOrFloat fused_func(IntOrFloat x, FloatOrObject y)\r\n```\r\n\r\nthe old names in the `__pyx_capi__` dictionary (which are retained as aliases for now) are:\r\n\r\n```\r\n__pyx_fuse_1_1fused_func\r\n__pyx_fuse_1_0fused_func\r\n__pyx_fuse_0_1fused_func\r\n__pyx_fuse_0_0fused_func\r\n```\r\n\r\nwhile the new names are:\r\n\r\n```\r\nfused_func[float,object]\r\nfused_func[float,float]\r\nfused_func[int,object]\r\nfused_func[int,float]\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe old values are kept for compatibility, and will be used if the new values aren't found (ensuring compatibility with old modules). I'd intend to remove this in the end but likely not any time soon.\r\n\r\nRelated to https://github.com/cython/cython/issues/7603 (vaguely)",
